# DEV_README

If you're editing this project, thanks.

The goal is simple: keep the viewer stable and keep changes easy to review.

## Keep It Clean

- Do not redesign stuff unless you are fixing a real visual issue.
- Avoid huge rewrites in one shot.
- If you remove code, explain why it is safe.
- Keep commits focused on one thing.

## Quick Test Before You Finish

1. Run it locally.
2. Load at least one real `.rhr` replay.
3. Confirm these still work:
   - play and pause
   - seek bar
   - speed changes
   - HUD updates
   - 3D field rendering
4. If parsing or timing changed, test with more than one replay.

## Code Notes

- Prefer clear names over short clever names.
- Replace unexplained constants with named constants when it improves clarity.
- Add comments only where the intent would otherwise be unclear.
- Keep browser support practical and avoid unnecessary platform-specific logic.

## If Behavior Changes, Update Docs

- `README.md` for user-facing changes.
- `CHANGELOG.md` for release notes.
- `docs/reverse-engineered.md` for reverse-engineered format and runtime notes.
